          <title>Celtics beat Grizzlies 117-103 and complete the first 6-0 trip in franchise history</title>
          <description><![CDATA[MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) — Jayson Tatum had 25 points and 14 rebounds, Al Horford scored 26 points and the Boston Celtics swept a six-game road trip for the first time in franchise history with a 117-103 win over the Memphis Grizzlies on Monday night.]]></description>
